<doc id="355660" wikidata="Q5365623" url="?curid=355660" title="Nairan">
<text>In the ancient Japanese government, was the inspection of documents submitted to the &quot;tennō&quot; (emperor), or the position held by those who performed the inspection. 

The &quot;tennō&quot; usually gave a to the regent (either a &quot;sesshō or kampaku&quot;).

