<doc id="355730" wikidata="Q3195201" url="?curid=355730" title="Kenneth Robeson">
<text>Kenneth Robeson was the house name used by Street &amp; Smith publications as the writer of their popular characters Doc Savage and later Avenger. Lester Dent wrote most of the Doc Savage stories; others credited under the Robeson name included:

* William G. Bogart
* Evelyn Coulson
* Harold A. Davis
* Lawrence Donovan
* Philip José Farmer
* Alan Hathway
* W. Ryerson Johnson
* Will Murray
* Ron Goulart

All 24 of the Avenger stories were written by Paul Ernst, using the Robeson house name. Robeson was credited on the cover of &quot;The Avenger&quot; magazine as &quot;the creator of Doc Savage.&quot;

